  "description": "Edvard Johan Folke Åkerberg, born on August 7th, 1893, in Vanstad, Malmöhus County, was a senior physician. He was the first child of Lorens Åkerberg, a reverend, and Martha Sjöbohm. Edvard married Elsa Hallberg, a pharmaceutical student, on June 20th, 19xx. They had two children, Stig and Monica. Stig, born in 1924, was a medical student. Edvard completed his matriculation examination in Malmö in 1913, graduated with a Bachelor of Medicine from Lund University in 1917, and obtained his medical license in Stockholm in 1924. He received further training in surgery at hospitals in Stockholm and Gothenburg from 1924 to 1933. He served as assistant senior physician at the surgical department of Örebro County Hospital from 1933 to 1940, and since 1940, he has been a senior physician and director of the county hospital in Alingsås. Edvard has written various papers in surgical disciplines, specializing in urological surgery."
